The paper discusses the use of formal concepts and closed itemsets for knowledge discovery, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses interestingness measures for these concepts, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the applicability of these measures to noisy data and ranking correlation, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR).
